{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":578,"text":"Look, I had second thoughts, really,"},{"time":2601,"text":"about whether I could talk about this"},{"time":4636,"text":"to such a vital and alive audience as you guys."},{"time":7676,"text":"Then I remembered the quote from Gloria Steinem,"},{"time":10266,"text":"which goes,"},{"time":11905,"text":"\"The truth will set you free,"},{"time":13836,"text":"but first it will piss you off.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":17795,"text":"So -- (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20063,"text":"So with that in mind, I'm going to set about"},{"time":22187,"text":"trying to do those things here,"},{"time":23778,"text":"and talk about dying in the 21st century."},{"time":25640,"text":"Now the first thing that will piss you off, undoubtedly,"},{"time":28040,"text":"is that all of us are, in fact, going to die"},{"time":30659,"text":"in the 21st century."},{"time":31733,"text":"There will be no exceptions to that."},{"time":34123,"text":"There are, apparently, about one in eight of you"},{"time":36780,"text":"who think you're immortal, on surveys, but --"},{"time":39304,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":41482,"text":"Unfortunately, that isn't going to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46095,"text":"While I give this talk, in the next 10 minutes,"},{"time":47748,"text":"a hundred million of my cells will die,"},{"time":51244,"text":"and over the course of today, 2,000 of my brain cells"},{"time":53838,"text":"will die and never come back,"},{"time":55979,"text":"so you could argue that the dying process"},{"time":58060,"text":"starts pretty early in the piece."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60138,"text":"Anyway, the second thing I want to say about dying in the"},{"time":62252,"text":"21st century, apart from it's going to happen to everybody,"},{"time":64617,"text":"is it's shaping up to be a bit of a train wreck"},{"time":67233,"text":"for most of us,"},{"time":69578,"text":"unless we do something to try and reclaim this process"},{"time":72547,"text":"from the rather inexorable trajectory that it's currently on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76264,"text":"So there you go. That's the truth."},{"time":78072,"text":"No doubt that will piss you off, and now let's see"},{"time":79503,"text":"whether we can set you free. I don't promise anything."},{"time":82479,"text":"Now, as you heard in the intro, I work in intensive care,"},{"time":85062,"text":"and I think I've kind of lived through the heyday"},{"time":88166,"text":"of intensive care. It's been a ride, man."},{"time":90173,"text":"This has been fantastic."},{"time":91373,"text":"We have machines that go ping."},{"time":92528,"text":"There's many of them up there."},{"time":94838,"text":"And we have some wizard technology which I think"},{"time":97582,"text":"has worked really well, and over the course of the time"},{"time":100094,"text":"I've worked in intensive care, the death rate"},{"time":102166,"text":"for males in Australia has halved,"},{"time":104536,"text":"and intensive care has had something to do with that."},{"time":106155,"text":"Certainly, a lot of the technologies that we use"},{"time":108163,"text":"have got something to do with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110383,"text":"So we have had tremendous success, and we kind of"},{"time":112887,"text":"got caught up in our own success quite a bit,"},{"time":115241,"text":"and we started using expressions like \"lifesaving.\""},{"time":118865,"text":"I really apologize to everybody for doing that,"},{"time":120999,"text":"because obviously, we don't."},{"time":122229,"text":"What we do is prolong people's lives,"},{"time":124757,"text":"and delay death,"},{"time":126858,"text":"and redirect death, but we can't, strictly speaking,"},{"time":129703,"text":"save lives on any sort of permanent basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132558,"text":"And what's really happened over the period of time"},{"time":134543,"text":"that I've been working in intensive care is that"},{"time":137182,"text":"the people whose lives we started saving back in the '70s,"},{"time":140752,"text":"'80s, and '90s, are now coming to die in the 21st century"},{"time":145230,"text":"of diseases that we no longer have the answers to"},{"time":148830,"text":"in quite the way we did then."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151340,"text":"So what's happening now is there's been a big shift"},{"time":153215,"text":"in the way that people die,"},{"time":155022,"text":"and most of what they're dying of now isn't as amenable"},{"time":157293,"text":"to what we can do as what it used to be like"},{"time":160119,"text":"when I was doing this in the '80s and '90s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164030,"text":"So we kind of got a bit caught up with this,"},{"time":166894,"text":"and we haven't really squared with you guys about"},{"time":169927,"text":"what's really happening now, and it's about time we did."},{"time":173982,"text":"I kind of woke up to this bit in the late '90s"},{"time":177373,"text":"when I met this guy."},{"time":179467,"text":"This guy is called Jim, Jim Smith, and he looked like this."},{"time":183824,"text":"I was called down to the ward to see him."},{"time":186127,"text":"His is the little hand."},{"time":188372,"text":"I was called down to the ward to see him"},{"time":189758,"text":"by a respiratory physician."},{"time":190852,"text":"He said, \"Look, there's a guy down here."},{"time":193028,"text":"He's got pneumonia,"},{"time":194628,"text":"and he looks like he needs intensive care."},{"time":197133,"text":"His daughter's here and she wants everything possible"},{"time":199207,"text":"to be done.\""},{"time":201738,"text":"Which is a familiar phrase to us."},{"time":204357,"text":"So I go down to the ward and see Jim,"},{"time":206188,"text":"and his skin his translucent like this."},{"time":207873,"text":"You can see his bones through the skin."},{"time":210123,"text":"He's very, very thin,"},{"time":211661,"text":"and he is, indeed, very sick with pneumonia,"},{"time":215043,"text":"and he's too sick to talk to me,"},{"time":216524,"text":"so I talk to his daughter Kathleen, and I say to her,"},{"time":221674,"text":"\"Did you and Jim ever talk about"},{"time":224638,"text":"what you would want done"},{"time":226321,"text":"if he ended up in this kind of situation?\""},{"time":228335,"text":"And she looked at me and said, \"No, of course not!\""},{"time":232064,"text":"I thought, \"Okay. Take this steady.\""},{"time":237124,"text":"And I got talking to her, and after a while, she said to me,"},{"time":239968,"text":"\"You know, we always thought there'd be time.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":242971,"text":"Jim was 94. (Laughter)"},{"time":246737,"text":"And I realized that something wasn't happening here."},{"time":249271,"text":"There wasn't this dialogue going on"},{"time":250595,"text":"that I imagined was happening."},{"time":253248,"text":"So a group of us started doing survey work,"},{"time":256255,"text":"and we looked at four and a half thousand nursing home"},{"time":258475,"text":"residents in Newcastle, in the Newcastle area,"},{"time":261815,"text":"and discovered that only one in a hundred of them"},{"time":264762,"text":"had a plan about what to do when their hearts stopped beating."},{"time":267827,"text":"One in a hundred."},{"time":268966,"text":"And only one in 500 of them had plan about what to do"},{"time":272307,"text":"if they became seriously ill."},{"time":275404,"text":"And I realized, of course, this dialogue"},{"time":278164,"text":"is definitely not occurring in the public at large."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282800,"text":"Now, I work in acute care."},{"time":284278,"text":"This is John Hunter Hospital."},{"time":286383,"text":"And I thought, surely, we do better than that."},{"time":290384,"text":"So a colleague of mine from nursing called Lisa Shaw and I"},{"time":293380,"text":"went through hundreds and hundreds of sets of notes"},{"time":295896,"text":"in the medical records department"},{"time":297169,"text":"looking at whether there was any sign at all"},{"time":299790,"text":"that anybody had had any conversation about"},{"time":302218,"text":"what might happen to them if the treatment they were"},{"time":304071,"text":"receiving was unsuccessful to the point that they would die."},{"time":307415,"text":"And we didn't find a single record of any preference"},{"time":310356,"text":"about goals, treatments or outcomes from any"},{"time":314200,"text":"of the sets of notes initiated by a doctor or by a patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318770,"text":"So we started to realize"},{"time":321487,"text":"that we had a problem,"},{"time":323688,"text":"and the problem is more serious because of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328711,"text":"What we know is that obviously we are all going to die,"},{"time":332013,"text":"but how we die is actually really important,"},{"time":334678,"text":"obviously not just to us, but also to how that"},{"time":338233,"text":"features in the lives of all the people who live on afterwards."},{"time":341367,"text":"How we die lives on in the minds of everybody"},{"time":343688,"text":"who survives us, and"},{"time":346805,"text":"the stress created in families by dying is enormous,"},{"time":350537,"text":"and in fact you get seven times as much stress by dying"},{"time":353223,"text":"in intensive care as by dying just about anywhere else,"},{"time":355960,"text":"so dying in intensive care is not your top option"},{"time":359038,"text":"if you've got a choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361496,"text":"And, if that wasn't bad enough, of course,"},{"time":363665,"text":"all of this is rapidly progressing towards the fact that"},{"time":366313,"text":"many of you, in fact, about one in 10 of you at this point,"},{"time":368665,"text":"will die in intensive care."},{"time":370115,"text":"In the U.S., it's one in five."},{"time":371449,"text":"In Miami, it's three out of five people die in intensive care."},{"time":375199,"text":"So this is the sort of momentum"},{"time":377264,"text":"that we've got at the moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379552,"text":"The reason why this is all happening is due to this,"},{"time":382097,"text":"and I do have to take you through what this is about."},{"time":383399,"text":"These are the four ways to go."},{"time":385364,"text":"So one of these will happen to all of us."},{"time":388229,"text":"The ones you may know most about are the ones"},{"time":390759,"text":"that are becoming increasingly of historical interest:"},{"time":393605,"text":"sudden death."},{"time":395022,"text":"It's quite likely in an audience this size"},{"time":396467,"text":"this won't happen to anybody here."},{"time":399018,"text":"Sudden death has become very rare."},{"time":400748,"text":"The death of Little Nell and Cordelia and all that sort of stuff"},{"time":403203,"text":"just doesn't happen anymore."},{"time":404876,"text":"The dying process of those with terminal illness"},{"time":407293,"text":"that we've just seen"},{"time":408325,"text":"occurs to younger people."},{"time":409940,"text":"By the time you've reached 80, this is unlikely to happen to you."},{"time":412790,"text":"Only one in 10 people who are over 80 will die of cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416205,"text":"The big growth industry are these."},{"time":421040,"text":"What you die of is increasing organ failure,"},{"time":424291,"text":"with your respiratory, cardiac, renal,"},{"time":426526,"text":"whatever organs packing up. Each of these"},{"time":428306,"text":"would be an admission to an acute care hospital,"},{"time":430909,"text":"at the end of which, or at some point during which,"},{"time":432878,"text":"somebody says, enough is enough, and we stop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435054,"text":"And this one's the biggest growth industry of all,"},{"time":437622,"text":"and at least six out of 10 of the people in this room"},{"time":440197,"text":"will die in this form, which is"},{"time":442759,"text":"the dwindling of capacity"},{"time":446653,"text":"with increasing frailty,"},{"time":448972,"text":"and frailty's an inevitable part of aging,"},{"time":451222,"text":"and increasing frailty is in fact the main thing"},{"time":453775,"text":"that people die of now,"},{"time":454824,"text":"and the last few years, or the last year of your life"},{"time":456952,"text":"is spent with a great deal of disability, unfortunately."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460967,"text":"Enjoying it so far? (Laughs)"},{"time":464351,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":467504,"text":"Sorry, I just feel such a, I feel such a Cassandra here."},{"time":470932,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":476090,"text":"What can I say that's positive? What's positive is"},{"time":477149,"text":"that this is happening at very great age, now."},{"time":479564,"text":"We are all, most of us, living to reach this point."},{"time":482309,"text":"You know, historically, we didn't do that."},{"time":484197,"text":"This is what happens to you"},{"time":485666,"text":"when you live to be a great age,"},{"time":488189,"text":"and unfortunately, increasing longevity does mean"},{"time":490078,"text":"more old age, not more youth."},{"time":492005,"text":"I'm sorry to say that. (Laughter)"},{"time":498098,"text":"What we did, anyway, look, what we did,"},{"time":499895,"text":"we didn't just take this lying down"},{"time":501422,"text":"at John Hunter Hospital and elsewhere."},{"time":502924,"text":"We've started a whole series of projects"},{"time":504546,"text":"to try and look about whether we could, in fact, involve"},{"time":507542,"text":"people much more in the way that things happen to them."},{"time":511036,"text":"But we realized, of course, that we are dealing"},{"time":512268,"text":"with cultural issues,"},{"time":514612,"text":"and this is, I love this Klimt painting,"},{"time":516471,"text":"because the more you look at it, the more you kind of get"},{"time":518676,"text":"the whole issue that's going on here,"},{"time":520695,"text":"which is clearly the separation of death from the living,"},{"time":524213,"text":"and the fear â€” Like, if you actually look,"},{"time":526093,"text":"there's one woman there"},{"time":527268,"text":"who has her eyes open."},{"time":529187,"text":"She's the one he's looking at,"},{"time":530872,"text":"and [she's] the one he's coming for. Can you see that?"},{"time":534100,"text":"She looks terrified."},{"time":535626,"text":"It's an amazing picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537319,"text":"Anyway, we had a major cultural issue."},{"time":539540,"text":"Clearly, people didn't want us to talk about death,"},{"time":541524,"text":"or, we thought that."},{"time":543019,"text":"So with loads of funding from the Federal Government"},{"time":544966,"text":"and the local Health Service, we introduced a thing"},{"time":546386,"text":"at John Hunter called Respecting Patient Choices."},{"time":549284,"text":"We trained hundreds of people to go to the wards"},{"time":552133,"text":"and talk to people about the fact that they would die,"},{"time":555276,"text":"and what would they prefer under those circumstances."},{"time":557562,"text":"They loved it. The families and the patients, they loved it."},{"time":561081,"text":"Ninety-eight percent of people really thought"},{"time":563541,"text":"this just should have been normal practice,"},{"time":564995,"text":"and that this is how things should work."},{"time":567378,"text":"And when they expressed wishes,"},{"time":569316,"text":"all of those wishes came true, as it were."},{"time":571289,"text":"We were able to make that happen for them."},{"time":573269,"text":"But then, when the funding ran out,"},{"time":575519,"text":"we went back to look six months later,"},{"time":577604,"text":"and everybody had stopped again,"},{"time":579871,"text":"and nobody was having these conversations anymore."},{"time":583064,"text":"So that was really kind of heartbreaking for us,"},{"time":585117,"text":"because we thought this was going to really take off."},{"time":587834,"text":"The cultural issue had reasserted itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591805,"text":"So here's the pitch:"},{"time":592960,"text":"I think it's important that we don't just get on this freeway"},{"time":597046,"text":"to ICU without thinking hard about whether or not"},{"time":599545,"text":"that's where we all want to end up,"},{"time":601338,"text":"particularly as we become older and increasingly frail"},{"time":603474,"text":"and ICU has less and less and less to offer us."},{"time":607128,"text":"There has to be a little side road"},{"time":609458,"text":"off there for people who don't want to go on that track."},{"time":613933,"text":"And I have one small idea,"},{"time":616569,"text":"and one big idea about what could happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621018,"text":"And this is the small idea."},{"time":622079,"text":"The small idea is, let's all of us"},{"time":624860,"text":"engage more with this in the way that Jason has illustrated."},{"time":628796,"text":"Why can't we have these kinds of conversations"},{"time":630849,"text":"with our own elders"},{"time":632170,"text":"and people who might be approaching this?"},{"time":634960,"text":"There are a couple of things you can do."},{"time":636794,"text":"One of them is, you can,"},{"time":638925,"text":"just ask this simple question. This question never fails."},{"time":641839,"text":"\"In the event that you became too sick to speak for yourself,"},{"time":645594,"text":"who would you like to speak for you?\""},{"time":648527,"text":"That's a really important question to ask people,"},{"time":650441,"text":"because giving people the control over who that is"},{"time":652464,"text":"produces an amazing outcome."},{"time":655772,"text":"The second thing you can say is,"},{"time":656918,"text":"\"Have you spoken to that person"},{"time":658416,"text":"about the things that are important to you"},{"time":660336,"text":"so that we've got a better idea of what it is we can do?\""},{"time":664490,"text":"So that's the little idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667012,"text":"The big idea, I think, is more political."},{"time":668506,"text":"I think we have to get onto this."},{"time":670457,"text":"I suggested we should have Occupy Death."},{"time":673519,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":676304,"text":"My wife said, \"Yeah, right, sit-ins in the mortuary."},{"time":678874,"text":"Yeah, yeah. Sure.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":681453,"text":"So that one didn't really run,"},{"time":683318,"text":"but I was very struck by this."},{"time":684988,"text":"Now, I'm an aging hippie."},{"time":686701,"text":"I don't know, I don't think I look like that anymore, but"},{"time":689198,"text":"I had, two of my kids were born at home in the '80s"},{"time":691698,"text":"when home birth was a big thing, and we baby boomers"},{"time":695166,"text":"are used to taking charge of the situation,"},{"time":697862,"text":"so if you just replace all these words of birth,"},{"time":701260,"text":"I like \"Peace, Love, Natural Death\" as an option."},{"time":704341,"text":"I do think we have to get political"},{"time":705857,"text":"and start to reclaim this process from"},{"time":708455,"text":"the medicalized model in which it's going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":710422,"text":"Now, listen, that sounds like a pitch for euthanasia."},{"time":712462,"text":"I want to make it absolutely crystal clear to you all,"},{"time":714654,"text":"I hate euthanasia. I think it's a sideshow."},{"time":717318,"text":"I don't think euthanasia matters."},{"time":719505,"text":"I actually think that,"},{"time":721656,"text":"in places like Oregon,"},{"time":724205,"text":"where you can have physician-assisted suicide,"},{"time":727677,"text":"you take a poisonous dose of stuff,"},{"time":729894,"text":"only half a percent of people ever do that."},{"time":731770,"text":"I'm more interested in what happens to the 99.5 percent"},{"time":734476,"text":"of people who don't want to do that."},{"time":736232,"text":"I think most people don't want to be dead,"},{"time":738566,"text":"but I do think most people want to have some control"},{"time":740663,"text":"over how their dying process proceeds."},{"time":743405,"text":"So I'm an opponent of euthanasia,"},{"time":744545,"text":"but I do think we have to give people back some control."},{"time":747198,"text":"It deprives euthanasia of its oxygen supply."},{"time":750671,"text":"I think we should be looking at stopping"},{"time":752023,"text":"the want for euthanasia,"},{"time":753062,"text":"not for making it illegal or legal or worrying about it at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757757,"text":"This is a quote from Dame Cicely Saunders,"},{"time":761333,"text":"whom I met when I was a medical student."},{"time":762702,"text":"She founded the hospice movement."},{"time":765581,"text":"And she said, \"You matter because you are,"},{"time":767772,"text":"and you matter to the last moment of your life.\""},{"time":770294,"text":"And I firmly believe that"},{"time":772551,"text":"that's the message that we have to carry forward."},{"time":775637,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}